Can you give us any more information?  I went back and started I20070323-1616 with the target platform pointed to itself.

I created a RCP template targeted for 3.0 (since you mentioned plugin.xml) and one targeted for 3.3.  Both projects ran correctly when launched from the Editor.

I can confirm that the problem is with my (upgraded) eclipse install. It does not appear with 33m6 or 33m7 clean install. It does appear with my install- regardless if using my default workspace or a fresh one. I believe it's probably not worth investigating this (unless you're interested to), so I'd like to alternatively ask- is there any good way to perform a clean eclipse install and at the same time take over all installed plugins (e.g. mylar, eclipseme etc as in my install)- even just automatically taking over the remote sites would help?

Thanks,
Andreas

Thanks for confirming.  Closing.

As for your question, I suggest using Update Manager (Help > Software Updates > Find and Install...) from the top level menu if you want to augment your installation.

If you have any further questions, please ask on the newsgroup:
http://www.eclipse.org/newsportal/thread.php?group=eclipse.platform
